   <refnamediv>
       <refname>beta_pdf  </refname>
               <refpurpose>beta probability distribution </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[pdf]=beta_pdf(x,a,b)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =   vector of components</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> a </term> =   beta distribution parameter, a  =   scalar or vector of the same size than x</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> b </term> =   beta distribution parameter b  =   scalar or vector of the same size than x</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> pdf </term> =   probability distribution function at each element of x of the beta(a,b) distribution</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Probability distribution function of the beta(a,b) distribution  NOTES: mean[(beta(a,b)] = a/(a+b), variance = ab/((a+b)*(a+b)*(a+b+1)).
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
y=beta_pdf(x,10,5)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
